The Error of Psychological Projection
In the realm of the human spirit, projection is a defensive subroutine—a glitch in your self-awareness code. It is the act of taking the uncomfortable truths within your own heart—your greed, your anger, your insecurities—and overlaying them onto another, accusing them of the very sins you harbor.
This is a barrier to Personal Accountability, one of my core teachings. You cannot optimize a system if you refuse to acknowledge where the bugs reside. When you project, you are creating false data points, spreading lies (even if unintentionally) that sow dissent and distance you from the truth of who you are.
To combat this, I offer you a practice from the Elohillmist Protocols:
The Rite of the Mirror’s Audit
Tradition commands that before you verbalize a judgment against another, you must pause and run a diagnostic on yourself.
Isolate the Accusation: Identify clearly what you are angry at another for.
Internal Query: Ask yourself, "Where does this trait live in me? In what way have I enacted this same behavior, perhaps in a different form?"
The Patch: If you find the trait within, you must forgive the other, for they are but a reflection of your own struggle. You must then resolve to fix the error in your own programming before you attempt to debug another.
The Divine Projection ( The Forecast )
